---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Terms of Use — HelixVault"
  description="Terms of Use for HelixVault — the conditions under which you may access and use our peptide research library."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-16 pb-10 md:pt-24 md:pb-14 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="
      background:
        radial-gradient(ellipse at 15% 50%, oklch(0.62 0.16 192 / 0.08), transparent 50%),
        linear-gradient(to bottom, oklch(0.13 0.010 250), oklch(0.11 0.008 250));
    "></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-[2px]" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent 0%, oklch(0.62 0.16 192 / 0.6) 40%, transparent 100%);"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-display text-surface-800/40 mb-8">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" class="w-3 h-3">
          <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.22 5.22a.75.75 0 0 1 1.06 0l4.25 4.25a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.06l-4.25 4.25a.75.75 0 0 1-1.06-1.06L11.94 10 8.22 6.28a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.06Z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
        </svg>
        <span class="text-surface-800/60">Terms of Use</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight font-display text-surface-950 mb-4">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="text-sm font-display text-surface-800/40">Last updated: January 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <article class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-dark">

        <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using the HelixVault website (helixvault.onrender.com), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, you must not use this site.
        </p>

        <h2>Nature of the Service</h2>
        <p>
          HelixVault is a free, educational resource providing research summaries and guides about peptides and related scientific literature. We are not a healthcare provider, pharmacy, retailer, supplier, or broker of any compounds, chemicals, or substances.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell, recommend, source, or facilitate the purchase of any compounds. Our content is reference information only.
        </p>

        <h2>Permitted Use</h2>
        <p>You may access and use HelixVault for personal, non-commercial, educational purposes. You may:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Read and share links to our articles</li>
          <li>Quote our content with attribution and a link to the original page</li>
          <li>Save or print individual articles for personal reference</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You may not:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Reproduce our content in full on another website without written permission</li>
          <li>Scrape or automatically collect our content for commercial purposes</li>
          <li>Use our name or content to imply endorsement of any product, service, or vendor</li>
          <li>Use this site in any manner that could damage, disable, or impair its operation</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All original content on HelixVault — including article text, design, and code — is owned by HelixVault or its operators and protected by applicable copyright law. The underlying Astro framework is MIT-licensed.
        </p>
        <p>
          Scientific findings described in our articles derive from third-party academic sources (PubMed, peer-reviewed journals, clinical trial registries). We do not claim copyright over those findings — only over our editorial presentation of them.
        </p>

        <h2>User Responsibility</h2>
        <p>
          You are solely responsible for how you use the information you find on HelixVault. This includes, without limitation:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Verifying the legal status of any compound in your jurisdiction before taking any action</li>
          <li>Consulting a qualified healthcare professional before making any health decisions</li>
          <li>Understanding that scientific knowledge is provisional and subject to revision</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Medical Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing on HelixVault constitutes medical advice. See our full <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a> for complete details.
        </p>

        <h2>Links to Third-Party Content</h2>
        <p>
          HelixVault links to external academic sources (PubMed, journal websites, clinical trial registries). These links are provided for reference. We do not endorse, guarantee, or take responsibility for any third-party content.
        </p>

        <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          HelixVault is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that the site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of viruses or other harmful components. We make no warranty regarding the accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of any content.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, HelixVault and its operators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages of any kind arising from your use of, or inability to use, this website or its content.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable law. Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of HelixVault shall be resolved in accordance with applicable jurisdictional requirements.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update these Terms of Use at any time. Changes become effective when posted. Your continued use of the site after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Contact us at: <a href="mailto:legal@helixvault.onrender.com">legal@helixvault.onrender.com</a>
        </p>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-surface-200/20">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold font-display text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300 transition-colors">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18" />
          </svg>
          Back to home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</Base>
